result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin C Phelps was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Battery to Law Enforcement Officers, Fire Fighters or Commission Wardens, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.20(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2::00 p.m.  State by DA Andrew Christenson.  Defendant present with Attorney Barb Privat.

Court recites agreement - defendant plea to count 3 - DRI counts 1 and 2.  DA concurs - dismiss repeater.  Attorney Privat concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.  

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY to count 3.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to count 3 as attempted.  Court DRI counts 1 and 2.  Court orders judgment of conviction be entered today.  DA confirms compliance with any victim/witness rights.  Sentencing argument by DA.  Sentencing argument by Attorney Privat.  Statement by the defendant.

Court orders SWD and places the defendant on probation for 24 months.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
Pay court costs.
Abide with all rules/recommendations as imposed by the supervising agent.
Obtain a high school diploma or equivalency.
Maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess/consume any alcohol, illegal drugs, or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Not to be on any premises that is licensed to sell alcohol by-the-drink.
